      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCK REVOLUTION (3) led over 1600m at Darwin last time and dug deep to score by 2.75 lengths. Improved again and looks well placed to repeat the dose. Has a low gate and keeps the handy 2kg claim. VANGUARD LEGEND (2) peaks and found a place behind the above the latest. Tries hard and is always a chance at this level. ICHIBAN (1) was out of the money when resuming from a spell over 1400m at Morphettville Parks. He's switched to Darwin's top barn and on a 28-day return and just missed in a trial at the Parks in between. Has the ability and the step up to the mile suits. The betting will be key. ANPHINA (6) was a big winner this grade over 1400m last time and will be better for it. The former Victorian will manage the mile and he has to be considered. EQUAL BALANCE (4) steps up plenty in trip on a 7-day return and may be the best of the rest.",
